items.text: Good durians at ground floor fruit stall by the escalator
02-02 is gd. ;) it's e jiao zi from margaret drive. came tues evening n many stalls not open
The chicken rice from Margaret drive is here and they are still good
There's an escalator in the middle of the building, connecting wet market @ 1st floor & food centre above. There r also fire escape stairwells @ each corner of the structure
the steamboat at ah pang so so nia ~
Sinheng Dessert, Chengteng with sweet potato! Nice as a replacement fr drink!
Lor mee is damn power.
Sin Kee Famous Chicken rice.
Avoid coming here past 1.30pm on weekdays. Most of the stalls are closed.
My personal loves: Ah Pang for old school hotpot (amazing soup and chilli), the lor mee shop is the only one my hokkien family doesnt complain about and the horfun at Shi Yun is stellar.
Sin Kee chicken rice: old skool classic. Last of the Mohicans
Tan Song Heng hokkien noodle old school and nice, still got sotong and pork!
Food, glorious food! The following here are worth trying:1. Fried Carrot Cake2. Wanton Noodles3. Hor Fun4. Duck Porridge
Must try the rojak at stall #02-1
#02-27 Food no good...
Mei ling chicken rice. One of it's kind. Mix n match.
Try the shi hui yuan's stall chicken feet hor fan! you will a chicken feet convert!

Fishball noodles. Hup Kee Teochew Fishball Mee #02-38 serves comforting bowl of noodles. Got the basics right: noodles cooked right & fragrant, fishball bouncy to chew, smooth her giao (fish dumpling)
Best fishball in Singapore
A place with cheap and good food
Gold Hill western food is good! Especially chicken chop and their fried rice.

DUCK! Been here for YEARS! And I truly recommend richard'd duck rice,just at the front of the market and also no signboard duck noodles! No signboard was frm the wet market at queenstown long time ago
No signboard duck rice / noodles it's a must for lor duck lovers.
Some of the stalls from Margaret Drive have moved here, including the guo tie and chicken rice.
Try the Hai Tang Lor Mee... Delicious and worth the money!
Try John Delicious Ramen  @ #02-08. A variety of dishes with handmade noodles as base.
Fruit juice stall!! Awesome!! Friendly AUNTY!! :))
Sin Kee Chicken rice is superb. They used to located at the old hawker ctr beside Queenstown MRT. Taste is still as yummy, price is reasonable. Worth the try
Not much stalls open on thurs night strange, try ah pang seafood steamboat also have Tze char not bad
Best claypot laksa!
Hai Tang Lor Mee #02-14 definitely one of the best in town
Gold Hill Western Food, mother & daughter in the store, try their F&C, love it esp to fish lovers
The Nasi Lemak Stall v nice ~
Vegetarian options: prata, thosai, beancurd, chee cheong fun, yam cake, yutiao, fried carrot cake, fruits, local desserts, yong tau foo, kueh, chwee kueh, peanut porridge, pumpkin cake
Phoenix carrot cake. Smallest portion 1.50, but without egg. 2.00 with egg  Never debate with the lady boss of the store and ask to pay 1.50 for carrot cake with egg. You'll be sorry if you did. ;)
无招牌卤鸭 Mei Ling Market & Food Centre Open 7:30am to 2pm Rest on Mon. Soup has nice herbal aroma. Porridge nice.
Chicken rice here bang for money,love the garlic as side!
Margaret drive fishball noodle! damn nice!
Hup Kee Fishball Mee hails from the old Margaret Drive Food Centre. Son took over from parents and food is still good!!
Try the tze char at #02-27! Good food for a reasonable price. But you have to wait awhile when its pack.
#02-14 lor mee must try
Love the chicken feet hor fun from shi hui yuan, must try!!
U guys muz try the shredded chicken hor fun...guarantee the 2nd day u wil queue up 4it!!!
老街坊 braised beef noodles is good
Hai Tang Lor Mee is a MUST TRY. Go for lesser noodles and top up with ingredients... It is worth it. :)
Must eat the Fishball noodles by LKY, yes his name is Li Guang Yao from qtps ..
Lor Mee is good , go try for it
Ah Pang steamboat is cheap but food served cannot make it. 
Famous for No Signboard Duck Rice & Sin Kee Chicken rice for lunch, but hidden gems are cze-char stalls during dinner...one for 古早味猪脚炒米粉，the other for 砂锅鱼头煲（ask for 红哥丽鱼）。
$3. I give credit to the noodles than the fish balls ✌️
Sin Kee Chicken Rice here is not the same stall as the previous Margaret Drive hawker centre.
Try the noodles from John Delicious Ramen and fish soup ! Very very good!^^ moved from opp queenstown mrt!
Sin kee chicken rice is awesome! Their raw fish is a must try!
The fruit juice store is v gd with a super friendly auntie that will recommend u a cocktail of juice to improve Yr health!
Don't eat the Mei ling strt wanton noodles! Try phoenix carrot cake either than the chix feet hor fun.
One of the best naturally ventilated HDB food centres I've visited!
The Hor Fun store is a MUST! not must try, but MUST EAT!
粿汁@美玲路肉骨茶、猪杂汤
SUPER NICE PLACE FOR LUNCH ^^ You will definitely enjoy this place!! :)
Nothing good here. Too many chicken rice stalls.
Fishball fans usually make a beeline for 新路 Fishball Noodle 02-05. Very condensed flavours with each bite
Hup kee teo chew fish ball mee is cheap and good!
Steamboat! Must try!
Tasty yet economical cze char. Opens for lunch and dinner
Ah Pang Seafood serves nice homey steamboat. Airy surroundings. More than enough seats, coz the rest of the food centre shuts down at night.
Hup Kee Fishball Noodle is great!
Have a bad experience with "Tong Xin Ju", the food there not fresh especially the prawn on the noodle. Nothing special.
Hup Kee Fishball mee is good. Tasty soup, large portion for a cheap price.
Must try You Huat Cooked Food the white beehoon is good and cheap
Some stalls are from ex Margaret drive hawker centre like sin kee chicken rice. Braised duck stall not bad, however Hokkien mee & chicken feet horfun are pretty average despite newspaper accolades.
新路鱼圆面。。 赞。
👲: Sin kee famous chicken rice is located here 🍗!
Playground downstairs @ base of Blk 158 for little ones to burn off some energy :-P
xin lu teochew fishball noodles (previously from margaret drive FC) - the fishballs are springy and the portion is generous! #bestvalue
add-on: think the 02-02 fried dumpling (Guo tie) is better than the steamed dumpling (jiao zi).
Duck noodles. No Signboard Braised Duck Noodles 02-04 serves old school style. Meat is tender, sauce tasted thick & smooth
Hai Tang Lor Mee....nice!! :) 02-14
Must try Mei Ling Street Homemade Carrot cake thumbs up. U must be patient with the old auntie coz she quite 4getful upon order she will ask u several times.
The Ipoh hor fun is still as good!!
